Police have arrested three suspects in connection with the​ murder of a 35-year-old man at Hemmingways mall in East London on Monday afternoon. “Police were summoned to a complaint of a person lying on the roadside in Two Rivers Drive, Dorchester Heights, Hemmingways,” said police spokesperson Sergeant Majola Nkohli on Tuesday. “At the scene, police found the lifeless body of a man, who was later identified as Mandisi Njokwana.” Njokwana had visible injuries in the upper body. “Preliminary investigation led to the arrest of three men aged between 32 and 34,” said Nkohli, adding that more arrests were imminent. The suspects are due to appear in court soon. DispatchLIVE